text: My heart goes out to everyone affected by the tragedy in Florida. Our schools and communities must always be safe places, free from senseless violence.
Sending my thoughts & prayers to the folks involved in the train crash earlier today. Glad to hear my colleagues @SteveDaines and @gianforte are safe.

Last night around 1 a.m., the Senate voted to pass the first major tax bill in a generation with support from only one party. The folks who voted yes on this bill did so at the expense of our kids and grandkids. They’re the ones who will be paying this tab long after we are gone.
Tonight, once again, Congress is proving to the American people that Washington is broken. The tax bill in front of us is the product of dysfunction, partisanship, and political desperation.
Elected officials must be held to a high standard, Al Franken is no exception. It’s time for him to step down.
